cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CC 

This paper presents a language for programming and proving properties of programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of equational reasoning and type-checking for managing equalities, which is related to logic in computer science (cs.LO). The focus on program verification and constructing terminating programs suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE). The use of a control operator and subtyping may also relate to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and compiler construction (cs.CC).
